Bonnie Somerville https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bonnie_Somerville 0 Bonnie Somerville (born February 24, 1974) is an American actress and singer. She has had roles in a number of movies and television series, most notably NYPD Blue, Grosse Pointe, Friends, The O.C., Cashmere Mafia, Kitchen Confidential, Without a Paddle, and Golden Boy. She starred as Dr. Christa Lorenson in season one of the CBS medical drama Code Black. Bonnie_Somerville ( born February_24_,_1974 ) is an_American_actress_and_singer .
